RACE.RACE_TEXT: REMINGTON PARK RACE 1 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 80. Claiming Purse 12000. FOR ACCREDITED OKLAHOMA-BREDS THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since August 15, 2023 Allowed 2 lbs. A Race Since July 15 Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MEGA BOND tracked the leader on the inside up the backstretch, saved ground around the turn and gained ground steadily through the final furlong to get up for the win in the final jump. JUST CHILLIN led the way on the inside up the backstretch, raced in the two path around the turn, dug in in the stretch and was nabbed at the wire. CINCO STEVE pressed the pace on the outside through the opening quarter of a mile, continued around the bend in the three path and was outkicked in the final furlong. J B'S LEGACY raced off the pace on the inside early, navigated the turn from the two path and improved position on the outside in late stretch. SHIPMAN'S SONG stalked the pace setters on the outside up the backstretch, raced in the four path around the bend and weakened in the lane. HOODOO BROWN raced off the pace on the outside through the early going, continued around the turn in the two path and showed no kick. CANONIZE trailed the field up the backstretch, raced in the three path around the turn and never threatened. CATALE STORM chased the leaders between horses early, navigated the bend from the four path and tired in the stretch.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: REMINGTON PARK RACE 2 1M Dirt CR: 75. Claiming Purse 12000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE MARCH 15, 2023 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 122 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: DANZIG UP A STORM saved ground around the first turn, dueled on the inside up the backstretch and around the far turn and shook clear in the final furlong. BRI raced in the two path early, dueled on the outside up the backstretch, continued to battle from the two path around the far bend and kept on to the finish. MUMBLEBEE raced in the three path around the first bend, chased the leader on the inside up the backstretch, navigated the far bend still in the three path and improved position late. GEORGIANO raced in the four path early, stalked the pace setters on the outside up the backstretch, came around the second turn in the three path and showed no kick. STAYTHIRSTYMYAMIGO trailed the field from the two path through the opening half mile, saved ground around the far bend and was not a threat. AWESOME SUNSET was acting up when the gates opened, causing her gate to open late, lost her rider in the process and was caught and walked off.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: REMINGTON PARK RACE 3 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 80. Claiming Purse 12000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE MARCH 15, 2023 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 122 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CRYSTAL CRESCENT raced in the middle of the pack between horses up the backstretch, began a bid from the three path coming around the turn and gained ground to get up for the win late. THINKITASADONATION dueled between horses through the opening quarter of a mile, continued to battle from the two path around the turn, and dug in in the lane but was caught in the final strides. WICKED STREET tracked the pace setters on the outside up the backstretch, navigated the bend from the two path and weakened in the final furlong. OKIE FRONT raced in the middle of the pack on the inside through the opening stages, came around the turn in the two path and finished evenly. GO GO GO raced in the middle of the pack between horses up the backstretch, continued around the turn in the three path and showed no kick. PROUD VALENTINE dueled on the inside up the backstretch, continued to battle while saving ground around the turn and tired entering the stretch. SHELL GAME raced in the middle of the pack between horses through the early going, navigated the bend from the three path and was empty from there. GIRONA raced off the pace on the outside up the backstretch, came around the turn in the four path and made no bid. HOPE AND A DREAM trailed the field up the backstretch, raced in the two path around the turn and was never a factor.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: REMINGTON PARK RACE 4 1 1/16M Dirt CR: 90. Claiming Purse 13000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since September 15 Allowed 2 lbs. Such A Race Since July 15 Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $7,500 (Races Where Entered For $5,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).

CLAIM.OWNER: Eleven One Racing Stables LLC (Kevin Roberts)
Orin A. Chain Revocable Living Trust

RACE.FOOTNOTES: MAU MAU raced in the three path around the first turn, settled off the pace on the inside for the run up the backstretch, saved ground around the far bend, began a bid passing the quarter pole and kicked clear. WHITAKER raced in the two path early, chased the pace setter on the outside up the backstretch, began a bid coming around the second turn, was carried out to the five path entering the stretch and chased the winner home from there. CLASSIC KING saved ground around the first bend, tracked the leader on the inside up the backstretch, began a bid passing the three eighths pole, floated wide into the stretch and was outkicked in the final furlong. TWITTY CITY raced off the pace in the four path between horses through the opening half mile, came around the far bend in the three path and was not a threat to the top three. KENTUCKY PEERLESS raced in the three path early, stalked the leaders on the outside up the backstretch, continued around the far turn in the four path and showed no kick. WILBERT led the way from the two path around the first turn and up the backstretch, gave way from the two path coming around the second turn and faded in the lane. NOMOREMRNICEGUY saved ground around the first turn, continued up the backstretch at the back of the pack on the outside, swung out to the five path coming around the second bend and was empty in the stretch.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: REMINGTON PARK RACE 5 1M Dirt CR: 99. Allowance Purse 35000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON A RACE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, OR STATE BRED OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 122 lbs. (If management deems it necessary to take this race off the Turf, it will be run at a distance of 1 Mile on the main track.) (Rail at 20 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SILENCE D'ORO led the way around the first turn and up the backstretch, saved ground around the far turn and held clear to the wire. PEPPER JACK raced in the middle of the pack on the inside through the opening half mile, saved ground around the far bend and chased the winner home. SPIRIT OF SPOATIE raced in the middle of the pack between horses through the early going, navigated the far turn from the two path and finished evenly. HOLY EMPEROR raced outside around the first turn, settled in the middle of the pack up the backstretch, continued around the far turn in the two path and raced evenly in the lane. MAHOMEY chased the leaders between horses through the opening half mile, navigated the second turn from the three path and faded in the stretch,. MOR VICTORY raced in the middle of the pack on the outside around the first turn and up the backstretch, came around the far bend in the three path and made no bid. WHITEROSE JEWEL trailed the field throughout and despite saving ground was not a threat.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: REMINGTON PARK RACE 6 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 62. Claiming Purse 15000. FOR ACCREDITED OKLAHOMA-BREDS FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 122 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: GRACE THE LADY chased the leaders up the backstretch, began a bid from the three path coming around the turn and got up for the win. REALITY CHECK dueled on the inside up the backstretch, saved ground around the turn, dug in in upper stretch and was caught late. HENNY'S CHICK raced off the pace on the inside early, saved ground around the turn, launched a bid in upper stretch and gained ground late. CAT TALE SKY bumped with the horse to her inside at the start, raced off the pace through the opening quarter, came around the bend in the two path and improved position in late stretch. LAMENTABLE JARIN raced at the back of the pack through the opening stages, saved ground around the bend and passed tiring horses in the lane. RAINING stalked the pace setters on the outside up the backstretch, navigated the turn from the three path and weakened in the stretch. HOT TAMALLI dueled on the outside up the backstretch, came around the bend in the two path and faded from there. LA PARADISO JORDAN veered out and bumped with the horse to her outside at the start, raced in the middle of the pack early, continued around the turn in the three path and was outkicked. BROWN LIAISON raced in the middle of the pack between horses through the opening stages, navigated the turn from the four path and was no threat. MY GOLDEN PRIZE trailed the field up the backstretch, moved up while racing five wide around the turn and flattened out in the lane. EUROROSE raced in the middle of the pack on the outside early, continued around the turn in the five path and was empty in the stretch.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: REMINGTON PARK RACE 9 1M Dirt CR: 74. Maiden Special Weight Purse 34000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE, FOUR, AND FIVE YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 117 lbs.; Older, 121 lbs. (Horses That Have Raced For $30,000 Or Less Will Be Least Preferred). (If management deems it necessary to take this race off the Turf, it will be r un at a distance of 1 Mile on the main track.) (Rail at 20 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: JAZZY LASSIE raced off the pace on the outside through the opening half mile, continued around the far turn still in the three path, began a bid approaching the quarter pole and kicked clear. OCCURRENCE saved ground early, chased the leaders up the backstretch, continued to save ground around the far bend and kept on to the finish. LEOPARD BAIT raced in the two path around the first turn, settled in the middle of the pack for the run up the backstretch, navigated the second turn from the four path and improved position in the lane. HOORAY FOR CREDIT saved ground around the first turn, dueled on the inside up the backstretch and around the far bend and faded in the final furlong. CINNAMON FACE dueled from the three path through the opening half mile, continued to battle from the two path around the far turn and tired entering the stretch. SHEZAPISTOL raced in the four path around the first bend, stalked the leader on the outside up the backstretch, continued around the far turn still in the four path and tired from there.
